
\Ssdiff\S:  Options

     -l   prints only the left column if the lines are identical.

     -o output_file   creates a file called <output_file> that is a combination
                      of lines from <file_name1> and <file_name2>.  Prompts the
                      user with a "%" for a decision on how to incorporate each
                      difference into the new file.  See the manual page for
                      details on this option.

     -s   suppresses the printing of identical lines

     -w width   changes the width of the output lines to <width> characters.
                The default and the maximum is 130.
